channel.title: Bypassing Windows Parental Controls for vista?
channel.description: Well recently my parents have put on parental controls for every user except theirs and I can't access anything like youtube.I have tried adding a new user through cmd and moving them to a local group but it still says access denied.At this point I don't know what to do I was going to try and key log my main administer account and get the password but I can't install any programs that require administrator access.Could anyone help me?And I don't want to make a new boot disc to do all that crap I just need some way to get the administers password,or get past parental controls.
